Durban - A man who allegedly walked into a building in Richard's Bay claiming he was carrying a bomb is due in court on Thursday. According to East Coast Radio the incident took place in a complex in Partridge Place. They further reported that police were called to the complex and the building had to be evacuated after reports that someone had threatened to kill everyone in the building. ECR says video footage which was released on social media, two armed policemen are seeing approaching the suspect who walks outside. They instruct him to put his hands in the air before he is made to lie flat on the ground. He faces a charge of bomb threat. Police are investigating a case of bomb threat after receiving a call about a possible explosive planted at Musgrave Centre on Monday. According to police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, the Explosives Unit members were alerted. "A search was conducted and nothing was found. A case of a bomb threat has been opened at the Berea police station for investigation." Daily News